layers.characters: When a user types into a text node or changes one of its properties, we generate a path to represent the text, and store it along with the text node. This way, sharing a file (e.g. to a client) allows them to see the design as-is.
layers.fontFamily: Whyte, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Ubuntu, Cantarell, "Noto Sans", sans-serif, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol"

layers.characters: In addition to this, a font file is not always loaded in memory even when it is available from the user's local machine. This is because font files can be big, there could be many of them, and they aren't needed until text is edited. This makes loading them at startup time potentially very expensive. As such, calling
